<h2>YouTube SEO for Local Businesses</h2>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="YouTube SEO formula showing title, description, tags, and thumbnail optimization" src="/images/blog/youtube-local-seo-formula.webp" /></p>
<p>Publishing a video without optimization is like opening a store with no sign. YouTube SEO determines whether your videos appear in search results or sit at zero views.</p>
<h3>Titles That Rank and Get Clicks</h3>
<p><strong>[Primary Keyword] + [Location] + [Benefit or Specificity]</strong></p>
<div class="table-wrap"><table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Weak Title</th>
<th>Strong Title</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Plumbing Tips</td>
<td>5 Plumbing Tips Every Austin Homeowner Needs</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Our Dental Office</td>
<td>Tour Our Family Dental Office in Portland, OR</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Roof Repair</td>
<td>How to Spot Roof Damage After a Storm (Dallas)</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></div>
<p>Keep titles under 60 characters. Front-load the keyword. Include your city name.</p>
<h3>Descriptions That Feed the Algorithm</h3>
<p>Write 200 to 300 words minimum. Structure every description:</p>
<ol>
<li><strong>First 2 sentences:</strong> What the video covers (include primary keyword)</li>
<li><strong>Middle:</strong> Detailed summary with secondary keywords and location mentions</li>
<li><strong>Business info:</strong> Name, address, phone, website URL</li>
<li><strong>Links:</strong> Related videos, booking page, social profiles</li>
<li><strong>Timestamps:</strong> Chapter markers for videos over 5 minutes</li>
</ol>
<h3>Tags and Hashtags</h3>
<p>Add 10 to 15 tags per video. Mix broad ("plumbing tips," "home repair") with local ("plumber Tampa," "Tampa plumbing company") and long-tail ("how to fix a running toilet Tampa"). Add 3 to 5 hashtags including #YourCity.</p>
<h3>Thumbnails That Earn Clicks</h3>
<p>Custom thumbnails increase click-through rate by up to 30%.</p>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Show a human face with a clear expression</li>
<li>[ ] Use large text (4 to 6 words maximum)</li>
<li>[ ] Choose bright, contrasting colors</li>
<li>[ ] Maintain consistent branding across all thumbnails</li>
<li>[ ] Size: 1280 x 720 pixels minimum</li>
</ul>
<h3>Closed Captions and Transcripts</h3>
<p>Upload accurate captions for every video. Corrected captions give the algorithm more text to index. They also support your overall <a href="/blog/eeat-google-quality-guide/">E-E-A-T</a> signals.</p>
<h2>Filming Videos on a Local Business Budget</h2>
<p>You do not need a $5,000 camera or a production team. The most effective local business videos look authentic, not polished.</p>
