<h3>Filming Tips for Non-Videographers</h3>
<p><strong>Audio matters more than video.</strong> A video shot on a phone with clear audio outperforms a 4K video with echo and background noise. Always use an external microphone.</p>
<p><strong>Use natural light when possible.</strong> Face a window. Avoid overhead fluorescent lighting.</p>
<p><strong>Keep videos between 3 and 8 minutes.</strong> For how-to content, 5 to 7 minutes is the sweet spot. YouTube rewards watch time, but only if viewers actually watch.</p>
<h3>Batch Filming Saves Time</h3>
<p>Block 2 to 3 hours once per month. Film 4 to 8 videos in a single session. Change your shirt between takes to make each video look different. Create a <a href="/blog/create-content-calendar-seo/">content calendar</a> for your videos and plan topics monthly.</p>
