<h3>Shorts Best Practices</h3>
<p>The sweet spot is 30 to 45 seconds. Hook viewers in the first 2 seconds. Add text overlays since many viewers watch without sound.</p>
<p>Post 3 to 5 Shorts per week if possible. You can <a href="/blog/repurpose-blog-content-social-media/">repurpose content for social media</a> by turning Shorts into Instagram Reels and TikToks. Film once, publish everywhere.</p>
<h2>How YouTube Supports Your Google Rankings</h2>
<p>YouTube and Google are the same company. That relationship creates ranking advantages no other video platform offers.</p>
<h3>YouTube Videos Appear in Google Search</h3>
<p>Google displays video carousels in search results for thousands of local queries. A local plumber with an optimized video can appear in both the video carousel and in the <a href="/glossary/local-pack/">local pack</a> with their <a href="/blog/optimize-google-business-profile/">Google Business Profile</a>. That is 2 spots on page 1 from a single piece of content.</p>
<h3>Embed Videos on Your Website</h3>
<p>Every YouTube video you create should also live on your website. Embedded videos increase time on page. Google measures <a href="/glossary/engagement/">engagement</a> signals. This supports your broader <a href="/blog/seo-small-business-guide/">SEO for small business</a> strategy.</p>
<h3>Link Your YouTube Channel to Your GBP</h3>
<p>Google Business Profile allows you to connect your YouTube channel. Videos you upload can appear directly on your GBP listing. A salon with 5 video tours and transformation clips on their GBP listing converts more profile visitors into bookings. Add <a href="/blog/google-posts-guide/">Google Business Profile posts</a> alongside your video strategy for maximum visibility.</p>
<h3>YouTube Builds E-E-A-T Signals</h3>
<p>A dentist who publishes educational videos demonstrates real expertise. A contractor showing completed projects proves real experience. These signals compound with your website content, reviews, and <a href="/blog/schema-markup-seo-guide/">schema markup</a> to build overall authority.</p>
